column14: Run the entire Belgium coast, the majority on sandy beaches with the crossing of the ports of Nieuwpoort, Blankenberge and Oostende. Cross 2 borders in one day.
The straight distance between A and B is only 25-30km meaning a big part of the track is composed of running the Dunkirk port with its industrial scenes and long digues.

column14: Pass the port of Calais - closest port to UK and connection to Dover - and the mythical Cap Gris Nez and Cap Blanc Nez with a finish on Digue Carnot in Boulogne Sur Mer.
